title: A frozen IPO market signals two positive things for stocks, CNBC's Jim Cramer says
description: "The incumbents are winning, and that means their earnings could be better than anyone thinks," CNBC's Jim Cramer said.

title: Moderna says it hopes to offer new vaccines for cancer, heart disease, and other conditions by 2030
description: Moderna's chief medical officer said advancements in mRNA technology since the outset of the Covid pandemic have ushered in a golden age for new vaccines.

title: These are the top 10 busiest airports in the world—5 of them are in the U.S.
description: Atlanta’s Hartsfield-Jackson international airport was the busiest airport in the world in 2022, according to Airports Council International's annual ranking.

title: Warren Buffett-backed BYD announces new shock absorption tech for premium EVs
description: Electric vehicle giant BYD is banking on new driver-assist technology to smooth out car rides and get the edge on its EV competition.

title: Outlook for credit access hits record low while inflation expectations jump, NY Fed survey shows
description: Those reporting that credit is much or somewhat harder to get than a year ago rose to 58.2%, the highest ever.

title: FBI warns against using public phone charging stations
description: The law enforcement agency said that bad actors had figured out how to infect phones with malware using public charging cables.

title: Apple's Mac shipments fall more than 40%, worse than major rivals
description: The year-over-year fall is the worst performance of the top five PC manufacturers and comes amid fears of a recession and weakened consumer demand, IDC said.

title: Treasury yields fall after data shows U.S. job growth slowed in March
description: The yield on the benchmark 10-year Treasury note slipped to 3.3626%, while the yield on the 30-year Treasury bond dipped to 3.5811%.

title: Uber-owned Careem launches spinout with $400 million investment from UAE tech holding company e&
description: Careem Technologies will focus on the growth of the company's "super app," which offers dozens of services beyond ride hailing in one app.

title: China is facing a population crisis but some women continue to say 'no' to having babies
description: Faced with an aging population and poised to be overtaken by India as the world's most populous country, China continues to struggle to boost its birth rate.
